# GHSA-36hh-v3qg-5jq4 -- pyo3 0.25.1 out-of-bounds read in the
# nth/nth_back iterator path (fixed in pyo3 0.29.0). pyo3 is vendored
# inside the temporalio python sdk's compiled rust bridge
# (site-packages/temporalio/bridge/Cargo.lock); it is not a dependency
# we declare or can override -- the bridge ships as a prebuilt wheel.
# temporalio 1.28.0 (the latest release) still pins pyo3 0.25.1, so
# there is no upgrade path on our side. the vulnerable code path is an
# internal iterator method the bridge does not expose to our workflow
# code. remove this entry once temporalio publishes a release built
# against pyo3 >= 0.29.0.
